(This has a better set of maps than the 1st map.)

We can only wait to find out what the Victoria CVO, Charles Milne's people discover as to the cause of this 2nd sheep outbreak. Logically there might (note 'might', not 'may') be an epidemiologic link, such as animals being moved fro one to the other unvaccinated. The die-off on the 1st was massive with some 80 dead sheep being recorded, so it might have been a dirty truck with bloody mud. It will be interesting to know what they find. This is a job for an epidemiologist with muddy boots and a sharp eye, and good hearing; shepherds and owners will tell you things you never expected. "But there are a number of other sheep that have died on the property over the preceding months. Significant numbers [have died] but because of the advanced state of decomposition of some of them, it's impossible to give a precise number." Whatever started it did so a while ago. A challenge. - Mod.MHJ]
